    "pre": [],
    "pre_narrative": "OCTOBER 16, 1962. The world stands on the edge of a cliff. For decades, the US and the Soviet Union have been enemies, but they have avoided direct fighting. That is about to change.\n\nAmerican spy planes have taken photos that prove the impossible: The Soviet Union is secretly building nuclear missile bases in Cuba, just 90 miles from Florida. If these missiles are finished, they can destroy Washington D.C. in less than 15 minutes.\n\nInside the White House, President Kennedy has called a secret meeting. The Generals want to bomb Cuba immediately. The Diplomats want to talk. You are an intelligence analyst in the room. Your job is to look at the evidence, listen to the arguments, and help the President make the hardest decision in history. The clock is ticking.",
    "post": [
      "General LeMay believed that showing force was the only way to stop the Soviets. Robert Kennedy believed in giving them a way to back down gracefully. Who was right?",
      "In the simulation, you saw that a Soviet submarine almost fired a nuclear torpedo because they thought the war had already started. How dangerous is miscommunication in a crisis?",
      "The 'Turkey Trade' (swapping US missiles for Soviet missiles) was kept secret for decades. Do you think the public had a right to know the truth at the time?"
    ]
