          "credit": "US DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE",
          "content": "### SURVEILLANCE LOG: MISSION 3101\n**DATE:** October 14-16, 1962\n**SECTOR:** San Cristobal, Cuba\n\n**FIELD ANALYSIS:**\nThe image on your screen is the 'smoking gun.' Major Richard Heyser's U-2 spy plane has returned with photos of Soviet SS-4 'Sandal' missiles. These are offensive nuclear weapons capable of destroying American cities like Dallas or St. Louis.\n\n**The Timeline Threat:**\nCIA experts have analyzed the photos. They see 'erector launchers' (equipment to lift the rocket) and fuel trucks. \n\n**CRITICAL INTEL:** We have a window of **10 to 13 days** before these missiles are ready to launch. Once they are ready, the United States will have zero warning time before an attack. The Atlantic Ocean can no longer protect us."
