          "image": "https://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/cuba62/navyflagplotroom.jpg",
          "credit": "US NAVY FLAG PLOT - AI",
          "content": "### THE NAVY FLAG PLOT\n\n**TIME:** 10:00 AM EST\n\nThe Quarantine is active. A massive fleet of US destroyers has formed a line in the ocean 500 miles from Cuba. The order is clear: Any ship crossing the line must stop and be searched. If they carry missiles, they will be turned back.\n\n**The Crisis Point:**\nTwo Soviet cargo ships, the *Gagarin* and the *Komiles*, are heading straight for the line. They are being protected by a Soviet submarine. \n\nThe President is personally managing the ships from the White House. The Navy Admirals are furious. They want to run the operation their way, but Kennedy knows that one trigger-happy sailor could start a nuclear war."
        },
        "legal": {
          "label": "Combat Rules",
          "image": "https://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/cuba62/plottingboard.jpg",
          "credit": "TRACKING BOARD - AI",
          "content": "### RULES OF ENGAGEMENT\n\nThe US Navy is hunting the Soviet submarines. But how do you force a sub to surface without sinking it?\n\n**The Procedure:**\nThe US informs Moscow that it will drop 'practice' depth charges (small explosives) to signal submarines to come to the surface. \n\n**The Danger:**\nThe Soviet submarine crew is deep underwater. It is 100 degrees inside the sub, the air is foul, and they are exhausted. They cannot hear the radio. When they hear the explosions of the 'practice' charges, will they know it's a signal? Or will they think the war has started and fire their torpedoes? We are poking a bear in the dark."
        },
        "intel": {
          "label": "The Submarine",
          "image": "https://dwaugh-edsim.github.io/projectimages/cuba62/shipstandoff-1.jpg",
          "credit": "US NAVY - AI",
          "content": "### CONTACT REPORT: B-59\n\nSonar has detected a Soviet submarine, the *B-59*.\n\n**Intelligence Failure:**\nUS Intelligence believes these submarines are armed only with regular torpedoes. \n\n**REALITY CHECK:**\nThe B-59 is actually carrying a **Nuclear Torpedo** with the power of the Hiroshima bomb. The Captain has the authority to launch it if he thinks his ship is being destroyed. The decision you make about dropping those depth charges could be the last decision of the civilized world."
        }
